@startuml seq_01_sign_up
title Sequence Diagram: UC-01 Sign Up

actor User
participant "User Web" as Frontend
participant "Auth Controller" as Controller
participant "Auth Service" as Service
participant "User Repository" as Repo
participant "Redis Cache" as Redis
participant "Email Service" as Email

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open Register page
User -> Frontend: (2.1) Enter email
User -> Frontend: (3.1) Submit email
Frontend -> Controller: (3.2) POST /api/auth/register-email {email}
Controller -> Service: (4.1) Validate email format
Service -> Repo: (5.1) Check whether email is already registered
Repo --> Service: (5.2) Email not found
Service -> Redis: (6.1) Generate & store OTP (TTL 5m)
Service -> Email: (7.1) Send OTP email
Email --> Service: (7.2) Email sent
Service --> Controller: (7.3) Success
Controller --> Frontend: (7.4) 200 OK (OTP sent)
Frontend --> User: (7.5) Prompt for OTP

User -> Frontend: (10.1) Enter received OTP
User -> Frontend: (11.1) Submit OTP
Frontend -> Controller: (11.2) POST /api/auth/verify-otp {email, otp}
Controller -> Service: (12.1) Verify OTP
Service -> Redis: (12.2) Check OTP
Redis --> Service: (12.3) OTP matches
Service -> Redis: (13.1) Generate & store verification token (TTL 15m)
Service --> Controller: (13.2) Success (verification token)
Controller --> Frontend: (13.3) 200 OK (verification token)
Frontend --> User: (13.4) Prompt for username/password

User -> Frontend: (15.1) Enter username and password
User -> Frontend: (16.1) Confirm registration
Frontend -> Controller: (16.2) POST /api/auth/register {email, username, password, token}
Controller -> Service: (17.1) Validate username and password
Service -> Redis: (17.2) Validate verification token
Redis --> Service: (17.3) Token valid
Service -> Repo: (17.4) Check username availability
Repo --> Service: (17.5) Username available
Service -> Service: (18.1) Hash password (bcrypt)
Service -> Repo: (18.2) Create user account
Repo --> Service: (18.3) User created
Service -> Service: (19.1) Generate access & refresh tokens
Service -> Redis: (20.1) Store auth state (refresh token)
Service -> Redis: (20.2) Delete verification token
Service --> Controller: (21.1) Tokens & user info
Controller --> Frontend: (21.2) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (21.3) Log user in and redirect to home page
@enduml
